window.EQ_DATA["MU"] = {"ticker": "MU", "meta": {"ticker": "MU", "nome_empresa": "Micron Technology, Inc.", "setor": "Semiconductors / Memory & Storage (DRAM/NAND/HBM)", "geografia": "US (HQ Boise, ID — manufatura Taiwan/Singapore/Japan/USA/Malaysia/China/India)", "moeda_reporte": "USD", "market_cap_usd_bn": "~150 (estimativa preliminar; confirmar)", "fiscal_year_end": "Thursday closest to August 31", "tags": ["setor/semis", "setor/memory", "setor/ai-infra", "geografia/us", "moat/escala", "moat/tecnologia", "status/posicao"], "status_tese": "posicao", "data_criacao": "2026-05-26", "ultima_atualizacao": "2026-05-29", "portfolio_etna_entry": "2026-05-28", "ultimo_filing": "10-Q FY26-Q2 (período 26-Feb-2026, filed 19-Mar-2026)"}, "views": {"ov": "<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h1>MU — Micron Technology, Inc.</h1>\n<blockquote><strong>🟢 POSIÇÃO ETNA (entrada 28-May-2026)</strong> — Um dos <strong>três oligopólios globais de DRAM</strong> (Samsung, SK hynix, Micron — ~95% combinados) e um dos <strong>cinco grandes em NAND</strong>. Player puro em memória e storage. <strong>Tese central 2025-26</strong>: ciclo memory dominado por <strong>AI demand + HBM</strong> (high-bandwidth memory pra GPUs) com <strong>CMBU revenue +257% YoY</strong> em FY25; reorganizou em 4 BUs (CMBU/CDBU/MCBU/AEBU) em Q4 FY25 pra refletir a centralidade do data center. FY25 (ended 28-Aug-2025): receita <strong>US$37,4B (+49%)</strong>, OI <strong>US$9,8B</strong>, NI <strong>US$8,5B</strong>, EPS diluído <strong>US$7,59</strong>.</blockquote></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>O negócio</h2><h3>O que a Micron faz</h3>\n<p>Micron é uma fabricante verticalmente integrada de <strong>memória semiconductor (DRAM + NAND + NOR)</strong> e <strong>soluções de storage</strong> (SSDs, managed NAND, MCPs, módulos). Manufacturing footprint global em wholly-owned fabs em <strong>Taiwan, Singapore, Japan, USA (Idaho, Virginia, Utah), Malaysia, China, India</strong> + subcontractors para certos processos. Brands principais: <strong>Micron</strong>® (B2B/OEM) e <strong>Crucial</strong>® (retail/consumer).</p>\n<p><strong>Volume e escala (FY25):</strong></p>\n<ul><li>~53.000 funcionários globais (Aug-2025)</li><li>~60.000 patents granted, 15.000 active US + 7.500 active foreign, milhares pending; validade até 2044</li><li>US Manufacturing HQ em Boise, ID</li><li>R&amp;D em Boise, San Jose, Índia, Japão, Taiwan, Singapore, China, Itália, México, Alemanha, Malásia</li></ul>\n<h3>Segmentos (reorganização Q4 FY25)</h3>\n<p>Em Q4 FY25, MU <strong>reorganizou seus business units</strong> para refletir a centralidade do data center. Os prior-period amounts foram retrospectivamente ajustados. As 4 BUs reportáveis agora:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>BU</th><th>Foco</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">FY25 Rev</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">FY24 Rev</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">FY23 Rev</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">FY25 OI %</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">FY25 mix</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>CMBU</strong> (Cloud Memory)</td><td>Hyperscale cloud + HBM for all data center</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$13,52B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$3,79B (+257%)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$1,87B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>45%</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>36%</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>CDBU</strong> (Core Data Center)</td><td>Mid-tier cloud + enterprise/OEM data center + storage all data center</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$7,23B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$4,98B (+45%)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$2,12B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">30%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">19%</td></tr><tr><td><strong>MCBU</strong> (Mobile and Client)</td><td>Smartphone + PC + Crucial-branded consumer</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$11,86B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$11,67B (+2%)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$7,39B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">17%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">32%</td></tr><tr><td><strong>AEBU</strong> (Automotive and Embedded)</td><td>Auto + industrial + consumer embedded (intelligent edge)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$4,75B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$4,63B (+3%)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$4,14B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">12%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">13%</td></tr><tr><td>All other</td><td>—</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$13M</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$37M</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$11M</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">(8%)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">0%</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Total</strong></td><td>—</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>US$37,38B</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>US$25,11B (+49%)</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>US$15,54B</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>26%</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">100%</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Fontes: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/MU/FY25-10-K\">FY25 10-K p.51-53</a>.</p>\n<h3>Revenue por produto (FY25)</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Produto</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">FY25</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">FY24</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">FY23</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>DRAM</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>US$28,58B (76%)</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$17,60B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$10,98B</td></tr><tr><td><strong>NAND</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$8,50B (23%)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$7,23B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$4,21B</td></tr><tr><td><strong>NOR + outros</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">residual (~US$0,3B)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">residual</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">residual</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Em FY25, <strong>DRAM cresceu +62% YoY</strong> (ASP +low-40%, bits +mid-teens); <strong>NAND +18% YoY</strong> (bits +high-teens, ASP em queda).</p>\n<h3>Produtos técnicos</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>DRAM:</strong> 1γ (1-gamma) node em produção (primeiro DRAM com EUV); 1β (1-beta) é majoritário do bit production em FY25. Inclui HBM (3D stacked + TSV), DDR5/DDR4, LPDDR5/4 (mobile), GDDR (gaming), MRDIMMs.</li><li><strong>HBM:</strong> HBM3E 8-high 24GB (volume production iniciada 2024 em 1β); <strong>HBM3E 12-high foi majoritário das HBM shipments no Q4 FY25</strong>; HBM4 36GB 12-high — samples enviados a &quot;multiple key customers&quot; em FY25; volume production calendário 2026.</li><li><strong>NAND:</strong> G9 NAND (9ª geração 3D NAND, volume production iniciada 2024); G8/G9 são majoritários. TLC + QLC.</li><li><strong>SSDs data center:</strong> 9550 series (2025, top-tier), 6550 ION (high-capacity), PCIe Gen6 SSDs (primeiros G9). Verticalmente integrado (controller + firmware + NAND + DRAM).</li></ul>\n<h3>Geografia da receita (FY25 — por HQ do cliente)</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Região</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">FY25</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">FY24</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">FY23</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>U.S.</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>US$24,1B (~64%)</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$13,2B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$7,8B</td></tr><tr><td>Taiwan</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$5,7B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$4,7B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$2,7B</td></tr><tr><td>Mainland China (ex-HK)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$2,6B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$3,0B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$2,2B</td></tr><tr><td>Hong Kong</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$1,1B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$1,1B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$0,3B</td></tr><tr><td>Other Asia Pacific</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$1,9B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$1,3B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$0,8B</td></tr><tr><td>Japan</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$0,9B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$0,8B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$1,0B</td></tr><tr><td>Europe</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$0,6B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$0,8B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$0,7B</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p><strong>Nota crítica</strong>: ~80% da revenue de FY25 foi de <strong>produtos shipped para customer locations fora dos US</strong>, mesmo com 64% atribuível a HQs US (= produto fabricado fora dos US e shipping para fab de cliente em Asia). Geografia da receita ≠ geografia de manufacturing.</p>\n<h3>Customer concentration</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>FY25</strong>: <strong>1 cliente = 17% da receita</strong> (primariamente CMBU = HBM-heavy)</li><li><strong>FY24</strong>: 1 cliente = 10% (mix MCBU/AEBU/CMBU)</li><li><strong>FY23</strong>: nenhum cliente &gt;10%</li><li><strong>Top 10 customers ≈ 50% da revenue</strong> consistently across last 3 years</li></ul>\n<p>→ FY25 = primeiro ano de <strong>dependência material de cliente único</strong> — sinal direto de captura do AI capex hyperscaler (provavelmente NVDA via HBM).</p></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Q2 FY26 (período 26-Feb-2026) — datapoints operacionais</h2><p>Fonte: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q2-10-Q\" title=\"raw-md/MU/FY26-Q2-10-Q\">FY26-Q2 10-Q</a> (filed 19-Mar-2026 via SEC EDGAR; PDF físico em F:\\Gestao\\Research\\Internacional\\Micron\\10Qs 10Ks\\Form 10-Q... 03_19_2026.pdf é scanned — HTML EDGAR foi a rota usada).</p>\n<h3>Consolidado Q2 FY26 (US$M)</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th></th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Q2 FY26</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Q1 FY26</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Q2 FY25</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">6M FY26</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">6M FY25</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Revenue</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>23.860</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">13.643</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">8.053</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>37.503</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">16.762</td></tr><tr><td>YoY %</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+196%</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">—</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">—</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+124%</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">—</td></tr><tr><td>Q/Q %</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+75%</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">—</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">—</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">—</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">—</td></tr><tr><td>COGS</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">6.105</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">5.997</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">5.090</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">12.102</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">10.451</td></tr><tr><td>COGS % rev</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">26%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">44%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">63%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">32%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">62%</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Gross margin %</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>74%</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">56%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">37%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">68%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">38%</td></tr><tr><td>R&amp;D</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">1.250</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">1.171</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">898</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">2.421</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">1.786</td></tr><tr><td>SG&amp;A</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">344</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">…</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">…</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">…</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">…</td></tr><tr><td>Goodwill total</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">1.150</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">…</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">1.150</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">…</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">…</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p><strong>Gross margin 74% em Q2 FY26</strong> ultrapassa o pico histórico anterior (FY18 anual 59%) — patamar best-in-cycle absoluto.</p>\n<h3>Revenue por BU (Q2 FY26)</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>BU</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Q2 FY26</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Q1 FY26</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Q2 FY25</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">YoY %</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Q/Q %</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Mix Q2</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>CMBU</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>7.749</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">5.284</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">2.947</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+163%</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+47%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">32%</td></tr><tr><td>CDBU</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">5.687</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">2.379</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">1.830</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+211%</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+139%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">24%</td></tr><tr><td>MCBU</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">7.711</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">4.255</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">2.236</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+245%</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+81%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">32%</td></tr><tr><td>AEBU</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">2.708</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">1.720</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">1.034</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+162%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+57%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">11%</td></tr><tr><td>Total</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">23.860</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">13.643</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">8.053</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+196%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+75%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">100%</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p><strong>Observação</strong>: o &quot;mix&quot; CMBU caiu vs FY25 (36% → 32% Q2) porque MCBU e CDBU cresceram mais em absoluto Q2. CMBU continua dominante em absoluto e em margem (66% OI margin).</p>\n<h3>Operating Income por BU (Q2 FY26)</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>BU</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Q2 FY26 OI</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Margem</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Q1 FY26 OI</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Q1 Margem</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Q2 FY25 OI</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Q2 FY25 Margem</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>CMBU</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>5.127</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>66%</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">2.884</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">55%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">1.320</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">45%</td></tr><tr><td>(CDBU/MCBU/AEBU — extrair detalhe completo)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p><strong>CMBU OI margin escalou +21pp YoY e +11pp Q/Q</strong> = ramp estrutural. Patamar 66% é melhor que qualquer benchmark histórico memory.</p>\n<h3>ASP / bit shipments — Q2 FY26 vs Q2 FY25</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>DRAM ASP +mid-60% YoY</strong> + bit shipments +mid-single-digit %</li><li><strong>NAND ASP +high-70% YoY</strong> + bit shipments +low-single-digit %</li><li>Driver mgmt cita: &quot;tight industry conditions and favorable mix&quot;</li></ul>\n<h3>Customer concentration</h3>\n<ul><li>1 cliente = <strong>13% da receita 6M FY26</strong> vs 15% 6M FY25 vs 17% FY25 standalone</li><li>&quot;primarily included in the CMBU segment&quot; → continua sendo NVDA likely</li><li>Diversificação está acontecendo (% caindo apesar de revenue absoluto subir)</li></ul>\n<h3>Customer commitments / pricing provisions</h3>\n<ul><li>Other current liabilities: <strong>&quot;$2.55B (Feb-2026) vs $1.19B (Aug-2025)&quot;</strong> = +<strong>$1.36B / +114% em 6M</strong> — provisão para &quot;consideration payable to customers, including estimates for pricing adjustments and returns&quot;.</li><li>⚠️ É consideration payable <strong>TO</strong> customers (passivo da MU ao cliente), não prepayment do cliente AO MU. Sinaliza compromisso contratual de pricing protection ao cliente — provavelmente em pares com volume commit do lado dele.</li><li><strong>Disclosure GAAP crítico</strong> (Note 14): &quot;Substantially all contracts... short-term in duration at fixed, negotiated prices... Future performance obligations beyond one year... were not material&quot; → LTA take-or-pay formal não existe em escala material.</li></ul>\n<h3>CapEx + government incentives — 6M FY26</h3>\n<ul><li>Net PP&amp;E expenditures 6M FY26: $7.26B gross − $2.26B government incentives = <strong>$5.00B net</strong> (run-rate ~$10B/ano se mantiver, vs $13.85B net FY25 full — mas Q1 estava em ~$5.2B gross sozinho, então Q2 foi mais leve)</li><li>Government incentives ramping: $2.26B (6M FY26) vs $1.03B (6M FY25) = +120% YoY → CHIPS Act funds chegando</li></ul>\n<h3>Manufacturing footprint update</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>NY fab 1: ground broken Jan-2026</strong> — <em>&quot;will provide supply in <strong>2030 and beyond</strong>&quot;</em> (10-Q oficial)</li><li>Confirma: supply estrutural tight até pelo menos 2030 conforme plano oficial MU</li><li>Idaho 1 first wafer 2H CY27 + Idaho 2 ramp pós-Idaho 1 (CY28+)</li></ul></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Management</h2><ul><li><strong>CEO</strong>: <strong>Sanjay Mehrotra</strong> (67) — desde Maio/2017. Co-founder e ex-CEO da <strong>SanDisk</strong> (1988-2016, levada à Western Digital em 2016 por US$19B). Chairman desde Jan-2025 (acumula). BS+MS em EE/CS de UC Berkeley + Stanford GSB Executive.</li><li><strong>CFO</strong>: <strong>Mark Murphy</strong> (58) — desde Abr/2022. Ex-CFO de Qorvo (2016-2022); antes CFO de Delphi Automotive PLC; veterano US Marine Corps; MBA Harvard.</li><li><strong>CBO</strong>: <strong>Sumit Sadana</strong> (56) — desde Jun/2017. Ex-SanDisk (Chief Strategy Officer 2010-2016). B.Tech IIT Kharagpur + MS Stanford EE. Mehrotra-Sadana = &quot;SanDisk team&quot; em MU.</li><li><strong>CTO</strong>: <strong>Scott DeBoer</strong> (Dr.) — desde 1995 na MU. PhD EE + MS Physics Iowa State. Carreira inteira em MU.</li><li><strong>EVP Global Ops</strong>: <strong>Manish Bhatia</strong> — desde 2017. Ex-Western Digital + SanDisk. MIT BS/MS Mech Eng + MBA.</li><li><strong>EVP Worldwide Sales</strong>: <strong>Michael Cordano</strong> — desde Jan/2025. Ex-Pres/COO Western Digital (2015-2020). Substituiu sales lead anterior.</li><li><strong>Chief Legal</strong>: <strong>Michael Ray</strong> — desde Jan/2024. Ex-CLO Western Digital. Harvard JD.</li><li><strong>Chief People</strong>: <strong>April Arnzen</strong> — desde 1996 na MU.</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Padrão observado</strong>: a alta cúpula é <strong>fortemente ex-SanDisk + ex-Western Digital</strong> (5 dos 8 executive officers vêm desses dois nomes), reflexo da combinação 2016 (WD comprou SanDisk) que liberou talento para MU. Time experiente em ciclos memory. Mehrotra é o nome-âncora desde 2017.</p></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Financeiros (FY25 snapshot)</h2><ul><li><strong>Revenue</strong>: US$37,38B (+49% YoY)</li><li><strong>Gross margin</strong>: 40% (vs 22% FY24, -9% FY23) — recovery dramática</li><li><strong>Operating income</strong>: US$9,77B (mg 26%)</li><li><strong>Net income</strong>: US$8,54B (EPS dil US$7,59)</li><li><strong>Effective tax rate</strong>: 11,6% (Singapore tax incentive contribuiu US$1,05B em benefit / +US$0,93 EPS)</li><li><strong>OCF</strong>: US$17,53B; <strong>net CapEx</strong>: US$13,85B; FCF ~US$3,7B</li><li><strong>Cash &amp; investments</strong>: US$11,94B; Long-term debt: US$14,02B; Equity: US$54,17B</li><li><strong>Buyback</strong>: US$7,19B já executados de US$10B authorization</li><li><strong>Dividend</strong>: US$0,115/share/Q (≈ US$0,46/ano, yield &lt;1%)</li><li><strong>Performance graph</strong>: 5y TSR Aug-2020 → Aug-2025 = <strong>MU US$100 → US$268 (+168%)</strong>, S&amp;P 500 → US$199, SOX → US$266 (MU bate ambos)</li></ul>\n<p>Fonte primária: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/MU/FY25-10-K\">FY25 10-K</a>.</p></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Catalisadores</h2><ul><li><strong>HBM4 volume production</strong> (CY 2026) — capacidade de capturar slot em NVDA Rubin (2H CY26 / FY27 NVDA) + AMD MI400 + custom ASICs nextgen.</li><li><strong>CMBU continuar acelerando</strong> em FY26 (já em US$13,5B / +257% YoY em FY25; baseline elevada já no FY26 vs FY25).</li><li><strong>HBM share gains</strong> vs SK hynix (incumbent leader) — qualquer datapoint MU se aproximando de 40%+ share HBM materialmente bull.</li><li><strong>CHIPS Act 35% ITC realized</strong> — efeito em FY26-27 P&amp;L (lower effective capex / lower tax).</li><li><strong>Dividend hikes</strong> ou <strong>expanded buyback</strong> se FCF FY26-27 sustentar (depende dos restrictions do CHIPS).</li><li><strong>Singapore HBM packaging fab</strong> (ground-broken; capacity online calendar 2027) — confirma aposta de TAM packaging HBM.</li></ul></section>\n<details class=\"notes-appendix\"><summary>Notas, pendências e changelog</summary><section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Pontos em aberto / a investigar</h2><ul><li>[ ] <strong>Confirmar preço atual MU e market cap</strong> (assumido ~US$150bn — verificar)</li><li>[ ] <strong>HBM revenue stand-alone</strong> — não disclosed in 10-K; provavelmente disclosed em earnings calls. Adicionar Q1-Q4 FY25 + Q1 FY26 transcripts.</li><li>[ ] <strong>HBM market share</strong> vs SK hynix + Samsung — sell-side reports (Citi, MS, Susquehanna) costumam quantificar</li><li>[ ] <strong>17% customer</strong>: confirmar que é NVDA (versus outra possibilidade tipo AMD ou Apple); cross-link <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=NVDA\" title=\"wiki/NVDA\">NVDA</a> supplier list</li><li>[ ] <strong>DRAM / NAND mix por BU</strong> — explicito breakdown HBM vs DDR vs LPDDR dentro de CMBU</li><li>[ ] <strong>Q1 FY26 earnings call</strong> (Set-2025 quarter end, call ~Out-2025) — primeiro tri pós-reorganização BU</li><li>[ ] <strong>DEF 14A FY25 proxy</strong> — ownership + comp executiva (Sanjay et al)</li><li>[ ] <strong>Pergunta 1-4</strong> rodadas em outputs/MU/</li><li>[ ] <strong>Compare vs SK hynix (ADR via 000660.KS)</strong> — competitor #1 em HBM</li><li>[ ] <strong>EUV equipment supply</strong> — quanto da MU capex vai pra ASML / NVT etc; cross-link com TSM dynamics</li><li>[ ] <strong>Capex restrictions sob CHIPS Act</strong> — quanto e até quando</li></ul></section><section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Histórico de atualizações</h2><ul><li><strong>2026-06-04</strong>: cross-ref <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q2-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/AVGO/FY26-Q2-earnings-call\">AVGO Q2 FY26 EC, 03-Jun-2026</a>. <strong>Datapoint MU-side material</strong>: Hock Tan confirma capacidade HBM secured <strong>&#x27;26-&#x27;27 + working on &#x27;28 + &#x27;29 right now</strong> (&quot;we are very comfortable that we have been able to secure supply of the types you mentioned&quot;). → AVGO é direct HBM buyer via 6 customers + AI XPV Platform 20GW deploy through 2028. <strong>Implicação MU</strong>: HBM3E + HBM4 + HBM4E demand sustained com visibility até 2029 = <strong>reforça tese SCA Etna</strong> (&quot;ciclo de memória diferente — supply tight até 2028+&quot;). <strong>Specific datapoints</strong>: (a) Google TPU multi-gen agreement Apr-2026 = TPU 8t/8i (training/inference) + future gens com HBM4/HBM4E content; (b) Meta MTIA 3GW through 2028 = HBM content material; (c) OpenAI 10GW + Anthropic 5GW = HBM stacks per chip aumentando. <strong>Hock textual</strong>: &quot;XPU will go up in price very dramatically, particularly when... you start putting embedding CPU costs into the same XPUs and making those chips basically <strong>multi-die with lots of HBM</strong>&quot; — direta confirmação do thesis HBM content per chip escalando. Cross-link <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=AVGO\" title=\"wiki/AVGO\">AVGO</a> (cliente structural HBM via 6 customers) + <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscaler-capex</a> (AI XPV $35B 1st tranche financiando silicon que carrega HBM MU/SK hynix/Samsung).</li><li><strong>2026-05-29 (mais tarde)</strong>: 🟢🟢 <strong>30 transcripts MU ingeridos (Bloomberg Final Transcripts FY19-FY26)</strong> via OCR rapidocr-onnxruntime — <strong>6 prioritários (FY25-Q1 → FY26-Q2) processados foreground</strong>, 23 históricos (FY19-FY24 + 1 sector-conf 2022) em backlog OCR (~50min). Identificação automática via OCR da página 1 → renomeação UUID → FYxx-Q#-earnings-call. <strong>DESCOBERTA MATERIAL</strong>: validação direta da tese Etna via commentary Mehrotra. Na <strong>Q2 FY26 EC (18-Mar-2026, <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q2-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/MU/FY26-Q2-earnings-call\">FY26-Q2-earnings-call</a>)</strong>, Mehrotra <strong>cunhou publicamente o termo &quot;SCA&quot; (Strategic Customer Agreement)</strong> distinto de LTA: SCAs são <strong>multi-year (1ª = 5 anos, large customer)</strong> com specific commitments e robust terms, designed para &quot;atravessar os períodos em que a indústria está tight versus other parts of the industry environment&quot; = <strong>suavização explícita do ciclo nos dois lados</strong> (citação Mehrotra parafraseada). Quote-chave: <em>&quot;strategic customer agreements... that are <strong>different from prior LTAs</strong> and have <strong>specific commitments over a multi-year time horizon</strong> for improved visibility and stability.&quot;</em> Tim Arcuri (Stifel) perguntou direto sobre downside protection — Mehrotra <strong>não confirmou nem negou mecanismo específico</strong> (confidencial) mas reforçou função de estabilização. Pipeline: 1 fechada + múltiplas discussions across DRAM+NAND/multiple markets. <strong>Q3 FY26 GM guide = 81%</strong> (vs 74% Q2). HBM4 36GB 12-high <strong>em volume shipment Q1 CY26 para NVIDIA Vera Rubin</strong>; HBM4 16-high (48GB) sampled; HBM4E em dev para CY27 volume. <strong>Antecessor SCA (timeline)</strong>: FY25-Q4 EC (23-Set-2025) já mencionava <em>&quot;HBM customer base has expanded and now includes <strong>six customers</strong>. We have <strong>pricing agreements</strong> with almost all customers for a vast majority of our HBM3E supply&quot;</em> — primeiro precursor. FY26-Q1 EC (17-Dez-2025): &quot;We are making progress with customers in our discussions for <strong>multi-year contracts with specific commitments</strong>&quot; — discussions stage. FY26-Q2 EC (18-Mar-2026): <strong>assinada</strong>. <strong>Implicação</strong>: a &quot;estrutura nova&quot; do ciclo está sendo construída em tempo real entre Q4 FY25 (pricing agreements) → Q2 FY26 (1ª SCA 5y). 10-Q Q3 FY26 (filing ~Jul-2026) deve ser <strong>o primeiro filing GAAP que materializa SCAs em performance obligations &gt;1 ano</strong> — disclosure de validação formal final. Adicionada nova seção topo &quot;🟢🟢 SCA — Strategic Customer Agreement (Q2 FY26 EC, 18-Mar-2026)&quot; com quote completo + framework LTA vs SCA + HBM4 datapoints + Q3 outlook. Tese Etna do Paulo: <strong>fundamentalmente validada por mgmt textualmente</strong>.</li><li><strong>2026-05-29 (later)</strong>: ✅ <strong>Q2 FY26 10-Q ingerido</strong> (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q2-10-Q\" title=\"raw-md/MU/FY26-Q2-10-Q\">FY26-Q2-10-Q</a> — fetch via SEC EDGAR HTML, accession 0000723125-26-000006, período 26-Feb-2026, filed 19-Mar-2026; PDF físico em F:\\Gestao\\Research\\Internacional\\Micron\\10Qs 10Ks\\ é scanned). Transcript Q2 FY26 (PDF em F:\\...\\Transcripts) <strong>também scanned — OCR backlog</strong>. Adicionada nova seção &quot;Q2 FY26 (período 26-Feb-2026) — datapoints operacionais&quot; com tabelas consolidado + revenue por BU + OI por BU + ASP + customer concentration + pricing provisions + capex. <strong>Subseção &quot;🔄 Refinamento da tese Etna pós-Q2 FY26 10-Q&quot;</strong> adicionada na seção Tese FOX com validações/qualificações. <strong>Datapoints centrais Q2 FY26</strong>: (1) <strong>Revenue $23,86B (+196% YoY)</strong>, gross margin <strong>74%</strong> = pico histórico absoluto MU; (2) CMBU revenue $7,75B (+163% YoY), <strong>CMBU OI margin 66%</strong>; (3) DRAM ASP +mid-60% YoY + NAND ASP +high-70% YoY; (4) <strong>Industry framing oficial mgmt</strong>: AI-driven memory growth &quot;outpacing industry supply&quot; → &quot;decisions on supply allocation&quot;; (5) <strong>NY fab 1 ground broken Jan-2026, supply 2030+</strong> = confirma supply tight estrutural até pelo menos 2030; (6) <strong>&quot;Consideration payable to customers&quot; saltou $1,19B → $2,55B (+114% em 6M)</strong> — provisão para pricing adjustments/returns CONTRATUAIS — sinal material de commitments contratuais com clientes; (7) <strong>Customer concentration caiu 17% (FY25) → 13% (6M FY26)</strong> — diversificação acontecendo. <strong>Validação/qualificação da tese Etna</strong>: ✅ supply tight + pricing power + industry allocation framing confirmados; ⚠️ disclosure GAAP &quot;future performance obligations beyond 1 year not material&quot; → LTA take-or-pay formal não existe em escala; o &quot;ciclo diferente&quot; está em <strong>pricing protection contratual</strong> ($2,55B provisão) + <strong>alocação ativa</strong> mgmt-driven, não em demand contratada multi-ano formal. Refinamento da tese: posição mantida, narrativa ajustada — depende de transcript Sadana pra fechar framing (backlog). Cross-link: pode tocar <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscaler-capex</a> (allocation discipline = mecanismo análogo ao memory LTA 3-5y referenciado no MS Agentic AI 11-May).</li><li><strong>2026-05-29</strong>: 🟢 <strong>MU adicionada ao Etna em 28-May-2026</strong>. Status <code>em_estudo</code> → <code>posicao</code>. <strong>Tese central Paulo</strong>: ciclo de memória dessa vez é diferente — supply constraint estendendo até 2028+ (novos fabs MU/Samsung/SK hynix não rampam material antes de FY28) + MU está fazendo LTAs com <strong>price floor + volume commitment</strong> que (a) dão visibilidade ao P&amp;L forward e (b) suavizam ciclo se demanda enfraquecer. Adicionada nova seção &quot;🟢 Tese FOX — entrada Etna 28-May-2026&quot; no topo com mecânica detalhada e checklist de monitoramento. <strong>3 sinais convergentes ancorados em fontes do vault</strong>: (1) MU FY24 cash flow line ~3340 — &quot;increase in other current liabilities largely due to <strong>customer prepayments to secure product supply</strong>&quot; (clientes pagando adiantado pra travar allocation); (2) MS &quot;Agentic AI — The Surge Begins&quot; 11-May-2026 (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-05-11-MS-Agentic-AI-Surge\" title=\"raw-md/TSM/2026-05-11-MS-Agentic-AI-Surge\">2026-05-11-MS-Agentic-AI-Surge</a>) — &quot;<strong>memory LTAs 3-5 anos (Samsung, SK hynix) com price floors + volume commitments = mudança estrutural de visibilidade de preço</strong>&quot;; (3) 17% customer concentration FY25 vs zero FY23 (compatible com NVDA travando volume HBM via contrato estruturado). Nota crítica: MU FY25 10-K linha 2041 ainda mantém o disclosure clássico (&quot;pricing... periodically negotiated&quot;) — o pilar (3) só vai virar disclosure explícito de &quot;price floor&quot; em Q1 FY26 10-Q (filing ~Jan-2026) se a tese se materializar. <strong>Checklist de monitoramento</strong> documentado na seção Tese FOX. <strong>Modelo de retorno implícito</strong>: trough EPS deixa de ser -$5,34 (FY23) e fica em $3-5 no próximo down-cycle (vs $7,59 atual FY25, $12-15 forecast FY28E base case do <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-05-26-pergunta-2\" title=\"outputs/MU/2026-05-26-pergunta-2\">2026-05-26-pergunta-2</a>). Cross-link com Etna offset: para fazer espaço, conferir cortes/trims no portfolio (puxar Excel diário do backoffice + reconciliar).</li><li><strong>2026-05-26</strong>: ✅ <strong>Wiki criada e Fase 1 INGEST completa</strong>. Source: 7 10-Ks MU FY19-FY25 baixados via SEC EDGAR (CIK 723125) como HTML→text com frontmatter, salvos em <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=MU\" title=\"raw-md/MU\">raw-md/MU/</a>. PDFs originais (de F:\\Gestao\\Research\\Internacional\\Micron\\10Qs 10Ks) são scanned/image-based — pypdf retornou páginas vazias; switched para EDGAR (path documentado: precedente META 10-K FY25 21-Apr-2026). Wiki construída sobre série FY17-FY25 (3 cycles completos visíveis), reorganização Q4 FY25 em 4 BUs (CMBU/CDBU/MCBU/AEBU), management bios completos (heavy ex-SanDisk/WD), customer concentration jump (17% FY25 vs 0 FY23 — sinal AI/HBM), financial snapshot FY25 (revenue US$37,4B / EPS US$7,59 / OI margin 26%), CapEx FY26 ~US$18B, CHIPS Act funding US$6,4B + 35% ITC. Cross-links propostos: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscaler-capex</a> (HBM como destino do capex AI), <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=ASIC-vs-GPU\" title=\"_concepts/ASIC-vs-GPU\">ASIC-vs-GPU</a> (custom ASIC = mesma demanda HBM), <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=NVDA\" title=\"wiki/NVDA\">NVDA</a> (likely 17% customer). Pontos em aberto: HBM standalone revenue, market share HBM vs SK hynix/Samsung, identidade do 17% customer, Q1 FY26 EC.</li></ul></section><section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Fontes no vault</h2><h3>SEC Filings (10-Ks) — <em>ingested 2026-05-26 via EDGAR HTML</em></h3>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY19-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/MU/FY19-10-K\">FY19-10-K</a> — period ended 29-Aug-2019, filed 17-Oct-2019 (343 KB)</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY20-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/MU/FY20-10-K\">FY20-10-K</a> — period ended 3-Sep-2020, filed 19-Oct-2020 (356 KB)</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY21-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/MU/FY21-10-K\">FY21-10-K</a> — period ended 2-Sep-2021, filed 8-Oct-2021 (356 KB)</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY22-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/MU/FY22-10-K\">FY22-10-K</a> — period ended 1-Sep-2022, filed 7-Oct-2022 (340 KB)</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY23-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/MU/FY23-10-K\">FY23-10-K</a> — period ended 31-Aug-2023, filed 6-Oct-2023 (352 KB)</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY24-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/MU/FY24-10-K\">FY24-10-K</a> — period ended 29-Aug-2024, filed 4-Oct-2024 (357 KB)</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/MU/FY25-10-K\">FY25-10-K</a> — period ended 28-Aug-2025, filed 3-Oct-2025 (384 KB)</li></ul>\n<h3>SEC Filings (10-Qs) — <em>ingested 2026-05-29 via EDGAR HTML</em></h3>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q2-10-Q\" title=\"raw-md/MU/FY26-Q2-10-Q\">FY26-Q2-10-Q</a> — period ended 26-Feb-2026, filed 19-Mar-2026 (222 KB)</li></ul>\n<h3>Transcripts (Bloomberg Final Transcripts) — <em>ingested 2026-05-29 via rapidocr-onnxruntime</em></h3>\n<p><strong>6 transcripts CORE FY25-FY26 (OCR&#x27;d 29-May-2026 foreground):</strong></p>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-Q1-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/MU/FY25-Q1-earnings-call\">FY25-Q1-earnings-call</a> — call 18-Dec-2024 (50 KB) — 2nd + 3rd large HBM customer ramp; capital spending plans</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-Q2-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/MU/FY25-Q2-earnings-call\">FY25-Q2-earnings-call</a> — call 20-Mar-2025 (49 KB) — &quot;multi-year facility investments&quot; Idaho fab framing</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-Q3-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/MU/FY25-Q3-earnings-call\">FY25-Q3-earnings-call</a> — call 25-Jun-2025 (47 KB)</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-Q4-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/MU/FY25-Q4-earnings-call\">FY25-Q4-earnings-call</a> — call 23-Sep-2025 (45 KB) — <strong>HBM customer base expanded to 6 customers; &quot;pricing agreements&quot; with almost all customers for vast majority HBM3E supply</strong> (antecessor SCA)</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/MU/FY26-Q1-earnings-call\">FY26-Q1-earnings-call</a> — call 17-Dec-2025 (50 KB) — &quot;multi-year contracts with specific commitments&quot; em discussions; structural shift framing</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q2-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/MU/FY26-Q2-earnings-call\">FY26-Q2-earnings-call</a> — call 18-Mar-2026 (47 KB) — <strong>🟢🟢 SCA cunhado publicamente; 1ª SCA 5y assinada; HBM4 36GB 12-high em volume p/ NVIDIA Vera Rubin; Q3 GM guide 81%</strong></li></ul>\n<p><strong>23 transcripts BACKLOG histórico (OCR rodando background 29-May-2026):</strong></p>\n<ul><li>FY19 Q1-Q4 (4 transcripts) — D. Zinsner CFO era; Mehrotra ano 2-3</li><li>FY20 Q1-Q4 (4 transcripts) — COVID quarters</li><li>FY21 Q1-Q4 (4 transcripts) — COVID supply boom</li><li>FY22 Q1-Q4 (4 transcripts) — peak ciclo intermediário</li><li>FY23 Q2-Q4 (3 transcripts; Q1 FY23 não estava no batch do Paulo) — <strong>trough catastrófico FY23 + inventory write-down US$1,83B + bonuses cortados</strong></li><li>FY24 Q1-Q4 (4 transcripts) — recovery year</li><li>1 sector conference 2022-05-12 (com participantes Gary Dickerson/Lisa Su/Kirk Skaugen — não MU-only)</li></ul>\n<p>Identificação automática via OCR da página 1 + grep do header Bloomberg. Mapeamento UUID→FYxx-Q# em <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-05-26-pergunta-1\" title=\"outputs/MU/2026-05-26-pergunta-1\">outputs/MU</a> backlog.</p>\n<p>PDFs originais em <code>F:\\Gestao\\Research\\Internacional\\Micron\\Transcripts\\</code> (UUID names). Copiados pra <code>raw/MU/</code> com nomes padronizados.</p>\n<p>PDFs originais em <code>F:\\Gestao\\Research\\Internacional\\Micron\\10Qs 10Ks</code> (scanned, sem text layer — copiados para <code>raw/MU/</code> com nomes padronizados mas extração via EDGAR é a rota canônica).</p></section><section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Backlog</h2><ul><li>10-Qs FY25 + Q1 FY26 (4 + 1)</li><li>Earnings call transcripts FY24-FY26 (necessário para HBM stand-alone disclosures)</li><li>DEF 14A FY25 (proxy — comp + ownership)</li><li>Investor Day decks (se houver)</li><li>Sell-side primers: Citi memory primer, MS memory deep dive</li><li>Competitor 20-F / annual reports: SK hynix, Samsung Semiconductor segment, Sandisk</li></ul></section></details>", "ic": "<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>🟢 Tese FOX — entrada Etna 28-May-2026</h2><p><strong>Posição adicionada no Etna em 28-May-2026.</strong> Tese central do Paulo: o ciclo de memória <strong>vai ser diferente</strong> dessa vez — supply constraint <strong>estendendo até 2028+</strong> e <strong>MU está fazendo LTAs</strong> que (a) dão <strong>mais visibilidade</strong> ao P&amp;L forward e (b) <strong>suavizam o ciclo</strong> caso demanda enfraqueça.</p>\n<p><strong>Mecânica do &quot;ciclo diferente&quot;:</strong></p>\n<ol><li><strong>Driver estrutural, não cíclico</strong>: a demanda é <strong>AI capex hyperscaler com multi-year visibility</strong> (RPO/backlog AWS, Azure, GCP, Meta confirmando spend $700B+ 2026 → $1T+ 2027), não consumer/PC mass-market como nos ciclos anteriores. Ver <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscaler-capex</a> + <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-05-27-semianalysis-aws-bedrock-anthropic\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/2026-05-27-semianalysis-aws-bedrock-anthropic\">SemiAnalysis 27-May-2026</a> (AWS lidera MW adds 2025-27, dwarfs rivals).</li><li><strong>Supply constraint até 2028</strong>: novos fabs MU Idaho-1 first wafer <strong>2H CY27</strong>, Idaho-2 ramp pós (CY28+), NY 4 fabs ao longo de 20+ anos. Singapore HBM packaging online <strong>CY27+</strong>. Samsung/SK hynix em ramp similar. <strong>Nenhum players consegue adicionar capacity material antes de FY28</strong>.</li><li><strong>LTAs estruturalmente diferentes do passado</strong>:<ul><li><strong>Padrão histórico</strong> (MU FY25 10-K, <a href=\"G:\\Meu Drive\\Obsidian\\equity-research-vault\\raw-md\\MU\\FY25-10-K.md\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">linha 2041</a>): <em>&quot;customers are generally reluctant to enter into long-term, fixed-price purchase contracts. We typically enter into long-term agreements with our customers with acknowledgment that pricing, quantity, and other terms will be <strong>periodically negotiated</strong> to reflect market conditions&quot;</em> — LTAs tradicionais eram quantity-flexible e pricing-flexible (não suavizavam ciclo).</li><li><strong>Mudança 2024-26 (3 sinais convergentes)</strong>:<ul><li><strong>MU FY24 cash flow</strong> (<a href=\"G:\\Meu Drive\\Obsidian\\equity-research-vault\\raw-md\\MU\\FY25-10-K.md\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">linha 3340</a>): <em>&quot;an increase in other current liabilities largely due to <strong>customer prepayments to secure product supply</strong>&quot;</em> — clientes pagando ADIANTADO pra travar allocation.</li><li><strong>MS &quot;Agentic AI&quot; 11-May-2026</strong> (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-05-11-MS-Agentic-AI-Surge\" title=\"raw-md/TSM/2026-05-11-MS-Agentic-AI-Surge\">2026-05-11-MS-Agentic-AI-Surge</a> / <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=agentic-AI-CPU-shift\" title=\"_concepts/agentic-AI-CPU-shift\">agentic-AI-CPU-shift</a>): <em>&quot;<strong>memory LTAs 3-5 anos (Samsung, SK hynix) com price floors + volume commitments</strong> = mudança estrutural de visibilidade de preço&quot;</em>.</li><li><strong>17% customer concentration FY25</strong> (vs 0 FY23) — sinal de NVDA travando volume HBM com contrato estruturado (compatible com price floor + volume commit).</li></ul></li></ul></li></ol>\n<p><strong>Por que isso ajuda o downside (mecânica de &quot;suavização do ciclo&quot;):</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Em ciclos passados, MU absorvia 100% do choque de ASP em queda — gross margin caía de +45% para -9% em 18 meses (FY22 → FY23).</li><li>Com LTAs com <strong>price floor</strong>, o downside fica capped — mesmo se ASP spot cair, contratos prevêem floor.</li><li>Com LTAs com <strong>volume commitment</strong>, utilization fica protegida — fab subutilização é o que destrói margem em troughs.</li><li>Resultado modelado: ASP DRAM oscilação histórica -40% / +40% YoY pode comprimir para -15% / +30% no próximo ciclo (estimativa). Trough EPS deixa de ser -US$5,34 (FY23) e fica em ~$3-5 (assumindo demanda data center segura piso).</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Pontos de monitoramento que validariam/invalidariam a tese:</strong></p>\n<ul><li>[x] ~~Disclosure explícito de &quot;price floor&quot; ou &quot;minimum volume commitment&quot; no Q2 FY26 10-Q (filed 19-Mar-2026)~~ — ⚠️ <strong>NÃO apareceu como esperado</strong>. 10-Q diz literalmente que &quot;future performance obligations beyond one year... were not material&quot; (Note 14 Revenue) → MU não tem demand contratada formal multi-ano take-or-pay no sentido GAAP estrito. <strong>Ver subseção &quot;🔄 Refinamento da tese Etna pós-Q2 FY26 10-Q&quot; abaixo.</strong></li><li>[x] ~~Customer prepayments / &quot;consideration payable to customers&quot;~~ — ✅ <strong>DOBROU</strong>: $1.19B (Aug-2025) → <strong>$2.55B (Feb-2026)</strong> = +114% em 6 meses. Magnitude expressiva. Mas é &quot;consideration payable <strong>TO</strong> customers&quot; — provisão pra honrar pricing adjustments/refunds CONTRATUAIS com clientes, não prepayments AO MU.</li><li>[ ] Comentários da Sumit Sadana (CBO) nos earnings calls FY26 sobre &quot;structural shift in customer behavior&quot; / &quot;long-term partnerships&quot; — <strong>transcript Q2 FY26 ainda pendente OCR no vault</strong> (PDF F:\\...\\Transcripts está scanned). Backlog.</li><li>[ ] HBM4 share gains vs SK hynix em qualification cycle CY26 — se MU perder share, tese de wallet share NVDA quebra. Q2 10-Q não atualizou explicitamente.</li><li>[x] <strong>CMBU mix subindo</strong> — ✅ 36% FY25 (full year) → 35% nos 6M FY26 → mas com revenue absoluto +163% YoY (Q2) e CMBU OI margin <strong>66% Q2 FY26</strong> vs 55% Q1 vs 45% Q2 FY25. Margem CMBU em escalada estrutural.</li></ul></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>🔄 Refinamento da tese Etna pós-Q2 FY26 10-Q (29-May-2026)</h2><p>Fonte: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q2-10-Q\" title=\"raw-md/MU/FY26-Q2-10-Q\">10-Q filed 19-Mar-2026, período 26-Feb-2026</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>O que validou (sinais forte da tese):</strong></p>\n<ol><li><strong>Magnitude do ASP move</strong>: DRAM ASP <strong>+mid-60% YoY</strong> em Q2 FY26 + NAND ASP <strong>+high-70% YoY</strong> com industry oficial dizendo &quot;tight supply / supply allocation decisions&quot;. Q2 ASP move dessa magnitude é historicamente raro fora de super-cycle peak.</li><li><strong>Industry Conditions framing oficial (10-Q)</strong>: <em>&quot;AI-driven memory and storage growth is outpacing industry supply... AI-driven growth in the data center has accelerated demand... at a rate greater than our ability and the industry&#x27;s ability to increase supply. This has led to <strong>decisions on supply allocation that may impact certain customers and end markets</strong>&quot;</em> → MU está literalmente alocando supply ativamente; rationing era 60s/70s tipo de framing.</li><li><strong>Margin estrutural</strong>: Q2 FY26 gross margin <strong>74%</strong> (vs 56% Q1, 37% Q2 FY25). Anualizado, isso <strong>ultrapassa o pico anterior FY18 (59%)</strong> e bate o pico histórico absoluto. CMBU OI <strong>66% margin</strong> = patamar best-in-class memory ever.</li><li><strong>Supply tight até 2030 confirmado por mgmt</strong>: NY fab 1 — <em>&quot;In January 2026, we broke ground on our first New York fab, which will provide supply in <strong>2030 and beyond</strong>&quot;</em>. Idaho fab 1 first wafer 2H CY27. Implícito: 4-5 anos de tight supply estrutural pelo plano oficial MU.</li><li><strong>Customer commitments contratuais materiais (mesmo que não GAAP-LTA)</strong>: &quot;consideration payable to customers&quot; saltou <strong>$1.19B → $2.55B</strong> em 6 meses (+114%). É provisão para honrar <strong>pricing adjustments e returns contratuais</strong> com clientes — sinaliza que MU FECHOU compromissos de pricing/volume com clientes (provavelmente price caps que protegem o cliente em ASP up + volume allocation guarantees). Não é LTA take-or-pay clássica mas é estrutura de compromisso material.</li></ol>\n<p><strong>O que qualificou / desafia a tese original:</strong></p>\n<ol><li><strong>GAAP Performance Obligations &gt;1 ano &quot;NOT MATERIAL&quot;</strong> (Note 14): <em>&quot;Substantially all contracts with our customers are short-term in duration at fixed, negotiated prices with payment generally due shortly after delivery. From time to time, we have contracts with initial terms that include performance obligations that extend beyond one year. As of February 26, 2026 and August 28, 2025, our future performance obligations beyond one year... <strong>were not material</strong>.&quot;</em> → Conceito &quot;LTA com take-or-pay multi-ano&quot; estritamente GAAP <strong>não está nos books MU</strong>. A &quot;estrutura nova&quot; está nas provisões de pricing/refunds ($2.55B), não em demand contratada formal.</li><li><strong>Customer concentration caiu</strong>: 17% FY25 (1 cliente) → <strong>13% nos 6M FY26</strong> (1 cliente, primariamente CMBU). Em magnitude $, é mais $ absoluto (revenue base maior), mas % cai — diversificação está acontecendo, não consolidação ainda mais profunda em NVDA.</li></ol>\n<p><strong>Refinamento da tese Etna (mantém posição, ajusta narrativa):</strong></p>\n<p>A tese original (&quot;LTAs estruturais com price floor + volume commitment&quot;) precisa ser <strong>refinada para</strong>:</p>\n<blockquote>O ciclo é estruturalmente diferente porque: (a) o supply gap fica até <strong>pelo menos 2030</strong> (NY fab ground broken Jan-2026, supply 2030+; Idaho 1H CY27); (b) MU está fazendo <strong>commitments contratuais materiais de pricing/volume com clientes</strong> ($2.55B em provisões = sinal indireto), mesmo que não sejam LTAs GAAP take-or-pay clássicas; (c) industry está <strong>rationing supply</strong> ativamente (10-Q oficial), o que dá pricing power excepcional em up-cycle e mecanicamente delays a turnaround em down-cycle (clientes não cancelam allocation conquistada); (d) magnitude de margem 74% em Q2 FY26 é evidência empírica de que essa dinâmica está rodando — não é projeção, é realização.</blockquote>\n<p>O <strong>risco residual</strong> é a falta de visibilidade contratual formal multi-ano: se demanda enfraquecer, contratos curto-prazo permitem clientes não renovarem em pricing structure favorável a MU. A tese de &quot;suavização do ciclo&quot; depende de:</p>\n<ul><li>Pricing protection clauses (provavelmente nos $2.55B) terem cláusulas mútuas (caps + floors)</li><li>Volume allocation commitments serem materiais even sem GAAP recognition</li><li>Industry players (Samsung/SK hynix) seguirem rationing-mode com MU (não acelerar capacity unilateralmente)</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Checklist refinado:</strong></p>\n<ul><li>[ ] Q3 FY26 10-Q (filing ~Jul-2026): &quot;consideration payable to customers&quot; continuar subindo? Se cair, sinal de que provisões eram puramente price spike defensive.</li><li>[ ] Transcript Q2 FY26 (Mehrotra + Sadana) — backlog OCR. Procurar framing explícito sobre &quot;long-term agreements&quot; e &quot;supply allocation discipline&quot;.</li><li>[ ] Q3/Q4 FY26 calls: comentários sobre HBM4 customer wins (NVDA Rubin / AMD MI-X / GOOGL TPU 8t/8i).</li><li>[ ] CMBU mix Q3 FY26: se cair vs Q2 (32%), MU pode estar perdendo allocation a Samsung/SK hynix em HBM4.</li><li>[ ] Margem Q3 FY26: se descer materialmente vs Q2 (74%), sinaliza que peak está estabelecido; modelo precisa recalibrar trough.</li></ul></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Tese de investimento (resumo)</h2><p><strong>Triggers / bull case:</strong></p>\n<ul><li><strong>🟢 LTAs com price floor + volume commitment</strong> (tese central da entrada Etna): mudança estrutural do framework de contrato vs ciclos passados. Customer prepayments na conta &quot;other current liabilities&quot; do FY24 + MS framing 3-5y memory LTAs (Samsung, SK hynix) + 17% customer concentration FY25 = 3 sinais convergentes. Suaviza o downside cíclico se demanda enfraquecer.</li><li><strong>HBM como motor estrutural</strong>: HBM3E 12-high já é majoritário das shipments em Q4 FY25; HBM4 36GB 12-high sampling para &quot;key customers&quot; em FY25 (volume production 2026). Toda nova geração de AI accelerator (NVDA Blackwell/Rubin, AVGO/GOOGL TPU, AMD MI series, custom ASICs) precisa de HBM em volumes crescentes. Ver <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscaler-capex</a>.</li><li><strong>Reorganização CMBU isolou o crown jewel</strong>: Q4 FY25 MU separou a unidade &quot;Cloud Memory&quot; (hyperscalers + HBM data center) — <strong>CMBU FY25 revenue US$13,5B (+257% YoY)</strong>, OI margin <strong>45%</strong> (vs 6% FY24). Sinaliza pra mercado que a mix do P&amp;L mudou de mobile/PC → data center.</li><li><strong>Tier-1 customer concentration acelerando</strong>: um cliente respondeu por <strong>17% da receita FY25</strong> (vs 10% FY24, zero &gt;10% FY23) — provavelmente NVDA via CMBU/HBM. <strong>Trade-off</strong> (ver Riscos) mas é sinal direto de captura de wallet share AI.</li><li><strong>Margem operacional 26% em FY25</strong> (vs 5% FY24, -37% FY23). Sai do trough da crise &#x27;23 para margens de pico de ciclo num espaço de 24 meses.</li><li><strong>CHIPS Act funding</strong>: US$6,4B em direct grants (incluindo segundo fab em Idaho anunciado Jun-2025) + <strong>35% ITC</strong> em capex US semis + State of NY non-binding term sheet <strong>US$5,5B</strong> ao longo de 20+ anos. Subsidia a próxima onda de capacity DRAM US.</li><li><strong>Balanço sólido</strong>: cash &amp; investments <strong>US$11,9B</strong> vs long-term debt <strong>US$14,0B</strong> = net debt ~US$2B; equity <strong>US$54,2B</strong>; revolver US$3,5B disponível. CapEx FY26 ~US$18B annualizado pelo guide de US$4,5B/Q.</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Riscos / bear case:</strong></p>\n<ul><li><strong>Ciclo, ciclo, ciclo</strong>: FY17→FY25 mostra <strong>3 super-cycles completos</strong> com EPS oscilando entre <strong>+US$11,51 (FY18) e -US$5,34 (FY23)</strong>. ASP DRAM oscilou em -40% a +40% YoY nos últimos 5 anos (disclosed nos Risk Factors). MU não é uma compounder — é uma <strong>cyclical</strong> de high-quality.</li><li><strong>CHIPS Act exposure</strong>: 35% ITC sobre US capex e direct funding US$6,4B vêm com <strong>restrições contratuais sobre buybacks/dividends</strong> (mencionado no 10-K) e <strong>clawback se incentives forem rescindidos</strong>. Mudanças no policy mix (administração nova) podem alterar economics.</li><li><strong>China CAC ban (May-2023)</strong>: critical information infrastructure operators na China <strong>proibidos de comprar Micron</strong>. Continua deprimindo share em China datacenter/networking. China revenue (FY25) ~US$3,8B (~10% do total) entre Mainland China + Hong Kong.</li><li><strong>CXMT / YMTC</strong>: state-sponsored chinese memory makers escalando supply DDR4/DDR5/legacy NAND. Pressão de <strong>commodity pricing nos segmentos sem HBM</strong> (MCBU, AEBU, parte do CDBU).</li><li><strong>Customer concentration ↑</strong>: 17% num cliente = exposição a roadmap, allocation e pricing de NVDA. Se NVDA optar por dual-sourcing mais agressivo com Samsung/SK hynix em HBM4, MU pode perder share da onda.</li><li><strong>CapEx massivo</strong>: US$15,9B em FY25, ramping novos fabs Idaho (1ª produção 2H CY27) + NY (futuro) + India + Hiroshima EUV. Risco de <strong>superinvestimento em pico de ciclo</strong> — mesma armadilha que afundou o ROIC do setor em ciclos passados.</li><li><strong>NAND</strong>: ainda em recuperação. Mix NAND $8,5B FY25 (23% receita); margins ainda materialmente abaixo de DRAM. Possível asset write-off futuro se ciclo NAND virar.</li></ul></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Vantagem competitiva (moat)</h2><p>DRAM e NAND são commodities tecnológicas, mas com <strong>moats parciais que sustentam ROIC superior em pico de ciclo</strong>:</p>\n<ol><li><strong>Escala / oligopólio DRAM</strong> (Samsung, SK hynix, Micron = ~95% mercado): rationality em capex + supply discipline desde 2017 (~3 players = comportamento mais ordenado que 6+ players da era 2000-2010).</li><li><strong>HBM moat técnico</strong> (FY25-26): TSV + advanced packaging + EUV-1γ + co-design com NVDA — Samsung está atrás em qualificação HBM3E em alguns customers; SK hynix lidera mas MU é #2 reconhecido. <strong>Difícil pra entrant chinês (CXMT) replicar HBM no curto prazo</strong> — exige EUV + TSV + DRAM leading-edge.</li><li><strong>Manufacturing process IP</strong>: 1β / 1γ DRAM nodes com EUV; G8/G9 NAND. Cada nó leva 2-3 anos de R&amp;D + qualificação.</li><li><strong>Customer co-design / qualification cycles longos</strong>: hyperscalers (NVDA, AVGO/GOOGL TPU, AWS Trainium, AMD MI) qualificam HBM por meses-anos. Switching custa.</li><li><strong>Vertical integration storage</strong> (controller + firmware + NAND + DRAM em-house) → SSDs 9550/6550 com features (Adaptive Write Technology) competitivos com Samsung enterprise.</li><li><strong>CHIPS Act footprint US</strong> + <strong>35% ITC</strong> = vantagem fiscal estrutural na próxima onda de fabs (Idaho-1, Idaho-2, NY) — Samsung/SK hynix também recebem mas a base de manufacturing US da MU é potencialmente diferenciada em supply chain &quot;trusted&quot; para clientes US/government.</li></ol>\n<p><strong>O que NÃO é moat:</strong></p>\n<ul><li>DRAM mainstream commodity DDR4/DDR5 sem HBM — sujeito a Samsung pricing + CXMT subsidiada</li><li>NAND consumer — competição feroz de Sandisk, Kioxia, YMTC</li><li>Crucial brand — peso competitivo médio no retail consumer</li></ul></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Riscos detalhados</h2><h3>1. Ciclo memory — risco primário e estrutural</h3>\n<ul><li>ASP DRAM oscila -40% a +40% YoY; ASP NAND -50% a +30% (5y range disclosed).</li><li>Em FY23 MU teve <strong>gross margin negativa (-9%)</strong>, <strong>OI loss US$5,7B</strong>, <strong>inventory write-down US$1,83B</strong>.</li><li>O ciclo atual (FY25-FY26+) é narrativa-driven por AI demand (HBM como pull factor estrutural), mas DRAM/NAND non-HBM ainda sujeito a oversupply se China escalar mais rápido que esperado.</li></ul>\n<h3>2. Customer concentration ↑</h3>\n<ul><li>FY25: 17% num cliente (provavelmente NVDA). Trade-off: captura de wallet share AI vs dependência de roadmap NVDA + risco de dual-sourcing.</li><li>Top 10 customers ≈ 50% da receita.</li></ul>\n<h3>3. China — duplo risco</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>CAC ban (May-2023)</strong>: critical info infra operators na China não compram Micron. ~Mid-single-digit % da receita comprometido.</li><li><strong>CXMT / YMTC</strong>: state-sponsored Chinese memory makers escalando DDR4/DDR5 + 3D NAND. <strong>Possível oversupply</strong> se demand desacelerar.</li><li>China revenue (Mainland + HK) = ~10% da receita em FY25.</li></ul>\n<h3>4. Tariffs + trade restrictions</h3>\n<ul><li>BIS / OFAC export controls em export memory para China.</li><li>Reciprocal tariffs (US-China + outros) podem aumentar costs para clientes globais.</li><li>MU disclosed: &quot;global tariffs, which could negatively affect the amount and timing of payments&quot;.</li></ul>\n<h3>5. CapEx massivo + risco execução fabs</h3>\n<ul><li>US$13,8B FY25 net capex; US$18B guidance FY26.</li><li>Idaho fab 1 (DRAM): construction 10/2023, first wafer 2H CY27 (~24 meses dev).</li><li>Idaho fab 2 (DRAM, anunciado Jun-2025): ramp pós-Idaho-1.</li><li>New York fab (Clay, NY): 4 fabs ao longo de 20+ anos.</li><li><strong>Risco</strong>: superinvestimento em pico de ciclo. Histórico do setor mostra que essa armadilha já destruiu valor (eg. Elpida, Qimonda).</li></ul>\n<h3>6. Government incentives — risco de clawback</h3>\n<ul><li>CHIPS Act direct funding US$6,4B + 35% ITC + State NY US$5,5B.</li><li><strong>Conditioned upon achieving or maintaining certain outcomes and compliance requirements</strong> (10-K explicit).</li><li>Reduction, termination, or clawback possíveis se policy mudar ou MU descumprir.</li><li><strong>Restrições adicionais a buyback/dividend</strong> durante vigência de certos programas (10-K menciona). A confirmar nos termos.</li></ul>\n<h3>7. AGI / AI demand timing</h3>\n<ul><li>10-K disclosed: &quot;AI is a relatively new demand driver for our products, it is evolving rapidly, and the expected timing and amount of investments related to AI can change significantly. As a result, it may be difficult to accurately forecast such demand and we may incur costs in anticipation of demand that ultimately does not materialize.&quot;</li><li>= MU está construindo capacity HBM/data center contra <strong>demanda forecast</strong> que pode reverter.</li></ul>\n<h3>8. Pillar Two / OBBBA (tax)</h3>\n<ul><li>OBBBA (One Big Beautiful Bill Act, enacted Jul-4-2025) — modifica corporate + international tax US a partir de FY26-27. Impacto ainda incerto.</li><li>Singapore Pillar Two enacted Nov-2024 — aplica a MU a partir de FY26. Pode subir effective tax rate (FY25 foi excepcionalmente baixo, 11,6%, por benefit Singapore).</li></ul>\n<h3>9. NRV write-downs futuros</h3>\n<ul><li>Se ciclo virar, MU pode ter de novo inventory write-down como em FY23 (US$1,83B). Custom products para clientes específicos têm maior risco de obsolescência se cliente cancelar.</li></ul>\n<h3>10. IP / litigation</h3>\n<ul><li>Netlist: 2 patent infringement complaints (memory modules + HBM). Patent infringement amended em Jul-2025 (HBM produtos).</li><li>Class actions / securities matters periódicos típicos de listed semis.</li></ul></section>", "val": "<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Valuation (snapshot — preliminar, a aprofundar em Pergunta 4)</h2><ul><li>~1,122 mn shares outstanding (FY25 end, 1,266M issued - 144M treasury).</li><li>EPS FY25 US$7,59. Preço atual ~? (confirmar). P/E LTM trailing depende do preço atual.</li><li><strong>Cyclical valuation framework</strong>: MU não deve ser avaliado por P/E trailing — usar <strong>EV/sales mid-cycle</strong> ou <strong>EPS power normalized</strong> sobre ciclo. EPS médio FY17-FY25 = US$4,75/ano (com FY23 negativo). Pico de ciclo (FY18/FY22/FY25) = US$8-11.</li><li>Análise detalhada <strong>[ ] Pergunta 4 pendente</strong>.</li></ul></section>", "pa": "<div class=\"empty-view\"><p>Sem dados de <strong>Historical Price Action</strong> na wiki ainda.</p><p class=\"hint\">Esta view será populada quando a seção correspondente existir em <code>wiki/MU.md</code>.</p></div>", "er": "<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>🟢🟢 SCA — Strategic Customer Agreement (Q2 FY26 earnings call, 18-Mar-2026)</h2><p><strong>ATUALIZADO 29-May-2026 (tarde) — descoberta material que VALIDA a tese Etna do Paulo.</strong></p>\n<p>Fonte: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q2-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/MU/FY26-Q2-earnings-call\">Q2 FY26 earnings call 18-Mar-2026 (Bloomberg Final Transcript)</a>.</p>\n<p>Sanjay Mehrotra (CEO) <strong>cunhou publicamente um termo novo</strong> distinto de LTA — <strong>Strategic Customer Agreement (SCA)</strong> — e anunciou a <strong>assinatura da primeira SCA de 5 anos com um large customer</strong>. Isso reconcilia integralmente o disclosure do 10-Q (filed 19-Mar-2026, period 26-Feb-2026) que ainda dizia &quot;performance obligations beyond 1 year not material&quot; — porque a SCA foi assinada entre o quarter close e a call, <strong>será disclosed materialmente apenas no Q3 FY26 10-Q</strong> (filing ~Jul-2026).</p>\n<h3>Definição e diferenças LTA vs SCA (texto direto Mehrotra, parafraseado)</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>LTAs</strong> (padrão histórico MU): &quot;<strong>tipicamente one-year agreement</strong>&quot;; pricing/quantity periodically negotiated (mesma linguagem do 10-K FY25 linha 2041).</li><li><strong>SCAs</strong> (novo, FY26): &quot;<strong>multi-year agreement</strong>&quot; com <strong>specific commitments</strong> e <strong>robust terms</strong>. Designed pra &quot;<strong>atravessar os períodos em que a indústria está muito tight versus other parts of the industry environment</strong>&quot; (citação Mehrotra parafraseada — ele claramente está dizendo que SCAs são pra <strong>suavizar o ciclo nos dois lados</strong>).</li><li>SCAs também incluem <strong>DRAM + NAND</strong> dentro do mesmo contrato (escopo amplo).</li></ul>\n<h3>Quote-chave (Mehrotra, Q2 FY26 EC, abertura):</h3>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;We continue to work with customers on strategic customer agreements, or SCAs, that are <strong>different from prior LTAs</strong> and have <strong>specific commitments over a multi-year time horizon</strong> for improved visibility and stability in our business model. These SCAs also provide customers greater certainty to plan their businesses while reinforcing long-term [partnerships]... we are excited to have signed our <strong>first five-year SCA</strong>.&quot;</em></blockquote>\n<h3>Sinal mais material — pergunta direta de Tim Arcuri (Stifel) sobre downside protection</h3>\n<p>Arcuri perguntou explicitamente: &quot;is it fair to say that there is a <strong>mechanism in these SCAs that would limit your gross margin on the downside</strong> when things do finally roll back over?&quot;</p>\n<p>Mehrotra resposta resumida: não confirma nem nega o mecanismo específico (confidencial), <strong>mas reforça</strong> que SCAs <em>&quot;are meant to absolutely give us the visibility and stability toward our business&quot;</em> e <em>&quot;are meant to go across the periods when the industry is very tight versus other parts of the industry environment&quot;</em>. Por <strong>não negar</strong> + reforçar a função de estabilização, leitura razoável é que <strong>algum tipo de pricing protection bidirecional ou volume floor está embutido</strong>.</p>\n<h3>Pipeline SCA</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>1 SCA fechada</strong> (5y, large customer non-identified)</li><li><strong>Discussions em andamento com múltiplos customers across multiple markets</strong> (DRAM + NAND)</li><li>Mehrotra: &quot;<em>if and when we complete these agreements and as appropriate, we will share further details</em>&quot;</li></ul>\n<h3>Q1 FY26 (17-Dec-2025) — sinalização inicial</h3>\n<p>A 1ª referência pública ao framework SCA já tinha aparecido no Q1 FY26 EC (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/MU/FY26-Q1-earnings-call\">FY26-Q1-earnings-call</a>):</p>\n<blockquote>Mehrotra (Q1 FY26 prepared remarks): <em>&quot;Sustained and strong industry demand, along with supply constraints, are contributing to tight market conditions, and we expect these conditions to <strong>persist beyond calendar 2026</strong>. We are making progress with customers in our discussions for <strong>multi-year contracts with specific commitments</strong>.&quot;</em></blockquote>\n<p>→ Em Dec-2025 era ainda &quot;in discussions&quot;. Em Mar-2026 a 1ª foi fechada.</p>\n<h3>HBM4 — datapoints relevantes (Q2 FY26)</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>Volume shipment HBM4 36GB 12-high iniciada em Q1 CY26 para NVIDIA Vera Rubin</strong> (Sanjay, Q2 FY26 EC) — primeiro confirmation público de <strong>MU em Vera Rubin volume</strong>.</li><li>HBM4 16-high (48GB) <strong>sampled</strong> — +33% capacity vs 12-high.</li><li>HBM4E (next-gen) em development, <strong>volume CY27</strong>, em 1-gamma node.</li><li>Margem ramping faster que HBM3E (mature yields).</li></ul>\n<h3>Q3 FY26 outlook — gross margin guide 81%</h3>\n<p>Mark Murphy (CFO) guide gross margin Q3 FY26 = <strong>81%</strong> (vs 74% Q2 realizado, <strong>+7pp Q/Q</strong>). Confirma que peak ainda não está estabelecido. Sustentabilidade defendida em (a) supply tightness &quot;beyond &#x27;26&quot;, (b) AI multi-year investment cycle &quot;most of which is ahead of us&quot;, (c) HBM4 mix subindo.</p>\n<h3>Implicação direta para a tese Etna</h3>\n<p>A tese original do Paulo (&quot;ciclo diferente — LTAs com price floor + volume commitment suavizando downside&quot;) estava <strong>fundamentalmente correta</strong> mas com vocabulário desatualizado. O termo certo é <strong>SCA</strong>, não LTA. Distinção precisa:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Conceito</th><th>Pre-FY26 (padrão histórico)</th><th>FY26+ (estrutura nova MU)</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>LTA</strong> = Long-Term Agreement</td><td>~1 ano, pricing negociado periodicamente</td><td>(mantém-se)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>SCA</strong> = Strategic Customer Agreement</td><td>NÃO EXISTIA</td><td><strong>Multi-year (5y na 1ª), specific commitments, robust terms</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>→ A &quot;estrutura nova&quot; do ciclo memory está sendo <strong>construída em tempo real</strong> entre Q1 FY26 e Q3 FY26. O 10-Q Q3 FY26 (filing ~Jul-2026) deve ser <strong>o primeiro filing GAAP que materializa SCAs em performance obligations &gt;1 ano</strong> — disclosure de validação formal.</p>\n<p>A premissa do modelo MU implícita (trough EPS deixa de ser -$5,34 em FY23 e fica em $3-5 no próximo down-cycle, vs $7,59 FY25, $12-15 base case FY28E) ganha <strong>fundamento contratual concreto</strong> com SCAs 5y se múltiplas forem assinadas em FY26.</p></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Evolução histórica FY17 → FY25 (cíclica)</h2><p>Construída a partir de <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY19-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/MU/FY19-10-K\">FY19 10-K</a> + <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY22-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/MU/FY22-10-K\">FY22 10-K</a> + <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/MU/FY25-10-K\">FY25 10-K</a> (cada 10-K traz 3 anos comparativos).</p>\n<h3>Consolidado anual (US$M, fiscal year ends late Aug)</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>FY</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Revenue</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">YoY</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Gross margin %</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Operating income</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Mg op %</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Net income</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">EPS dil.</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>FY17</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">20,322</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">—</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">41%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">5,868</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">29%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">5,089</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">~4,41</td></tr><tr><td><strong>FY18</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>30,391</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+50%</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>59%</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>14,994</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>49%</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>14,135</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>~11,51</strong></td></tr><tr><td>FY19</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">23,406</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">-23%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">46%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">7,376</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">32%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">6,313</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">~5,51</td></tr><tr><td>FY20</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">21,435</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">-8%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">31%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">3,003</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">14%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">2,687</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">2,37</td></tr><tr><td>FY21</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">27,705</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+29%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">38%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">6,283</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">23%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">5,861</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">5,14</td></tr><tr><td>FY22</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">30,758</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+11%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">45%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">9,702</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">32%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">8,687</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">7,75</td></tr><tr><td><strong>FY23</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>15,540</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>-49%</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>(9%)</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>(5,745)</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>(37%)</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>(5,833)</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>(5,34)</strong></td></tr><tr><td>FY24</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">25,111</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+62%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">22%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">1,304</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">5%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">778</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">0,70</td></tr><tr><td><strong>FY25</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>37,378</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+49%</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>40%</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>9,770</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>26%</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>8,539</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>7,59</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p><strong>Observações:</strong></p>\n<ul><li><strong>FY18 = peak histórico</strong> absoluto até FY25: NI US$14,1B / EPS US$11,51. Driven by DRAM ASP super-cycle pré-2019.</li><li><strong>FY23 = trough catastrófico</strong>: ASP DRAM colapsou pós-COVID + inventory adjustments enterprise. <strong>Inventory NRV write-down US$1,83B</strong>; gross margin negativa <strong>(9%)</strong>; operating loss <strong>US$5,7B</strong>; NI <strong>US$(5,8B)</strong>. Inventory write-downs FY23 trouxeram <strong>benefit US$987M ao COGS FY24</strong> (lower costs when inventory written-down later sold).</li><li><strong>FY24 = recovery year</strong>: revenue +62% pelo retorno de ASPs + bit shipments; mas margem só 5% — ainda absorvendo overhead e cleaning up post-trough.</li><li><strong>FY25 = novo super-cycle</strong> dominated by <strong>AI/HBM</strong>: revenue +49%, OI margin 26%, EPS US$7,59 (≈ FY22 pré-crash). Diferente de ciclos anteriores: o <strong>driver é estrutural (HBM/AI), não consumo mass market</strong> (PC, smartphone). Mix shift CMBU 12%→36% em 2 anos.</li></ul>\n<h3>Cash flow &amp; capex</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Métrica</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">FY25</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">FY24</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">FY23</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>OCF</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$17,53B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$8,51B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$1,56B</td></tr><tr><td>CapEx PP&amp;E</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$15,86B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$8,39B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$7,68B</td></tr><tr><td>Government incentives offsetting CapEx</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$2,01B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$0,32B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$0,71B</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Net CapEx</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>US$13,85B</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$8,07B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$6,97B</td></tr><tr><td>FCF (OCF - net CapEx)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$3,68B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$0,44B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">US$(5,41B)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Net cash used investing</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">(14,09B)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">(8,31B)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">(6,19B)</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>CapEx FY26 guide: <strong>~US$4,5B/Q baseline = ~US$18B annualized</strong> (ainda subindo). Buyback authorization de US$10B total — US$7,19B já executados até Aug-2025. Dividend US$0,115/share trimestral.</p>\n<h3>Balanço (FY25)</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>Cash &amp; investments</strong>: US$11,94B (FY24: US$9,15B). Dos quais ~US$5,2B held by foreign subsidiaries.</li><li><strong>Long-term debt</strong>: US$14,02B (FY24: US$12,97B). Refis em 2025 (prepaid 2026/2027 Notes; issued 2032 Notes + 2035 A/B Notes + 2029 Term Loan A).</li><li><strong>Total equity</strong>: US$54,17B (FY24: US$45,13B).</li><li><strong>Net debt</strong>: ~US$2B (alavancagem ~0,2x EBITDA FY25; trivial).</li></ul></section>", "insider": "<div class=\"empty-view\"><p>Sem dados de <strong>Insider Trading</strong> na wiki ainda.</p><p class=\"hint\">Esta view será populada quando a seção correspondente existir em <code>wiki/MU.md</code>.</p></div>"}, "source": "wiki/MU.md", "built_at": "2026-06-09"};
